<body>
<segment id="1" parent="1001" relname="preparation">Teach Disabled People to Take Care of a Pet</segment>
<segment id="2" parent="1002" relname="span">Pets make great friends for anyone ,</segment>
<segment id="3" parent="1003" relname="span">especially people</segment>
<segment id="4" parent="3" relname="elaboration">who have difficulty relating to others .</segment>
<segment id="5" parent="1006" relname="preparation">Steps</segment>
<segment id="6" parent="1008" relname="span">Considering Whether to Get a Pet</segment>
<segment id="7" parent="6" relname="elaboration">Not all people with disabilities are able to care for pets .</segment>
<segment id="8" parent="1009" relname="span">Carefully consider the person and their situation</segment>
<segment id="9" parent="1010" relname="span">when making a decision</segment>
<segment id="10" parent="1011" relname="span">about whether to buy a pet , and what type of pet</segment>
<segment id="11" parent="10" relname="purpose">to buy .</segment>
<segment id="12" parent="1015" relname="preparation">Notice how the person interacts with other animals .</segment>
<segment id="13" parent="14" relname="condition">If they are afraid of animals ,</segment>
<segment id="14" parent="1017" relname="span">then a pet is probably not a good idea .</segment>
<segment id="15" parent="1020" relname="condition">If they respond positively to animals ,</segment>
<segment id="16" parent="1020" relname="sequence">and know how to be gentle ,</segment>
<segment id="17" parent="1020" relname="sequence">then a pet might be a good idea .</segment>
<segment id="18" parent="1021" relname="same_unit">Getting over a fear of animals</segment>
<segment id="19" parent="1021" relname="same_unit">takes time and care .</segment>
<segment id="20" parent="1023" relname="span">A pet should only be gotten</segment>
<segment id="21" parent="20" relname="circumstance">once the person is pretty comfortable around animals .</segment>
<segment id="22" parent="1025" relname="span">Extremely fearful people might become afraid of a pet</segment>
<segment id="23" parent="22" relname="condition">if they have a bad experience .</segment>
<segment id="24" parent="1026" relname="span">Consider how rough or gentle a disabled child is .</segment>
<segment id="25" parent="1028" relname="span">A child</segment>
<segment id="26" parent="1029" relname="contrast">that breaks toys</segment>
<segment id="27" parent="1030" relname="same_unit">or hits others</segment>
<segment id="28" parent="1030" relname="same_unit">is not ready for a pet .</segment>
<segment id="29" parent="1032" relname="joint">They may upset the pet</segment>
<segment id="30" parent="1032" relname="joint">and get scratched or bitten .</segment>
<segment id="31" parent="1033" relname="span">Some disabled children are very tough .</segment>
<segment id="32" parent="1035" relname="span">Because hitting does n't hurt them ,</segment>
<segment id="33" parent="34" relname="attribution">they do n't realize</segment>
<segment id="34" parent="1036" relname="span">that it hurts others .</segment>
<segment id="35" parent="1039" relname="span">They need someone</segment>
<segment id="36" parent="35" relname="purpose">to explain this to them ,</segment>
<segment id="37" parent="1038" relname="joint">and to set rules .</segment>
<segment id="38" parent="1040" relname="span">Consider whether the disabled person understands personal space .</segment>
<segment id="39" parent="40" relname="condition">If they do n't ,</segment>
<segment id="40" parent="1043" relname="span">they may upset the pet ,</segment>
<segment id="41" parent="1042" relname="sequence">and get bitten/scratched .</segment>
<segment id="42" parent="1045" relname="span">The disabled person should be able to set boundaries</segment>
<segment id="43" parent="42" relname="elaboration">( and have others listen to those boundaries ) ,</segment>
<segment id="44" parent="1044" relname="joint">and should know how to respect others ' boundaries .</segment>
<segment id="45" parent="1047" relname="question">Does the disabled person respect other people 's boundaries ?</segment>
<segment id="46" parent="47" relname="condition">If so ,</segment>
<segment id="47" parent="1048" relname="span">they will probably respect a pet 's boundaries .</segment>
<segment id="48" parent="1050" relname="span">Do other people routinely violate the disabled person 's boundaries</segment>
<segment id="49" parent="48" relname="elaboration">( including personal space ) ?</segment>
<segment id="50" parent="1052" relname="condition">If so ,</segment>
<segment id="51" parent="52" relname="attribution">the disabled person will think</segment>
<segment id="52" parent="1052" relname="span">it 's okay to violate boundaries .</segment>
<segment id="53" parent="1054" relname="question">Is the person in compliance therapy ?</segment>
<segment id="54" parent="1056" relname="condition">If so ,</segment>
<segment id="55" parent="1057" relname="attribution">they may not realize</segment>
<segment id="56" parent="1057" relname="span">that people and animals are allowed to set boundaries ,</segment>
<segment id="57" parent="56" relname="elaboration">much less that these boundaries need to be honored .</segment>
<segment id="58" parent="1058" relname="sequence">Evaluate the person 's self-care abilities .</segment>
<segment id="59" parent="60" relname="condition">If they struggle to take care of themselves ,</segment>
<segment id="60" parent="1060" relname="span">then they may not be able to handle a pet .</segment>
<segment id="61" parent="1061" relname="joint">Do n't put extra responsibilities on an overtaxed person .</segment>
<segment id="62" parent="1063" relname="span">Alternatively ,</segment>
<segment id="63" parent="1064" relname="joint">if they are handling things well ,</segment>
<segment id="64" parent="1066" relname="attribution">and they say</segment>
<segment id="65" parent="66" relname="condition">they could handle a pet ,</segment>
<segment id="66" parent="1066" relname="span">then they are probably ready .</segment>
<segment id="67" parent="1067" relname="span">Consider how much care other household members can contribute .</segment>
<segment id="68" parent="1069" relname="same_unit">For example ,</segment>
<segment id="69" parent="1071" relname="condition">if a disabled girl 's dad is willing to clean up after it ,</segment>
<segment id="70" parent="1071" relname="joint">her brother will feed it ,</segment>
<segment id="71" parent="1072" relname="contrast">and her sister will walk it ,</segment>
<segment id="72" parent="1072" relname="contrast">then she may not need to be responsible for it .</segment>
<segment id="73" parent="1075" relname="joint">Talk to them ,</segment>
<segment id="74" parent="1076" relname="span">and see how much care</segment>
<segment id="75" parent="76" relname="attribution">they might think</segment>
<segment id="76" parent="1077" relname="span">they would be able to handle .</segment>
<segment id="77" parent="1075" relname="elaboration">Teaching the Disabled Person</segment>
<segment id="78" parent="1079" relname="span">Talk about personal space and pets .</segment>
<segment id="79" parent="1081" relname="preparation">Just like people ,</segment>
<segment id="80" parent="1081" relname="joint">pets have personal space</segment>
<segment id="81" parent="1082" relname="contrast">and do n't always want to play</segment>
<segment id="82" parent="1082" relname="contrast">or be petted .</segment>
<segment id="83" parent="1084" relname="joint">Encourage the person to pay attention to the pet 's body language ,</segment>
<segment id="84" parent="1085" relname="span">and to leave the pet alone</segment>
<segment id="85" parent="84" relname="condition">if it wants to be alone .</segment>
<segment id="86" parent="1087" relname="span">Encourage the person to call a pet</segment>
<segment id="87" parent="1088" relname="span">by holding out their hand</segment>
<segment id="88" parent="87" relname="elaboration">and/or making kissy sounds .</segment>
<segment id="89" parent="1091" relname="attribution">Explain</segment>
<segment id="90" parent="1091" relname="same_unit">that</segment>
<segment id="91" parent="92" relname="condition">if the pet wants to come ,</segment>
<segment id="92" parent="1092" relname="span">it will come .</segment>
<segment id="93" parent="94" relname="preparation">Otherwise , it wants alone time ,</segment>
<segment id="94" parent="1094" relname="span">so let it be .</segment>
<segment id="95" parent="1095" relname="joint">Explain how to avoid scaring a pet .</segment>
<segment id="96" parent="1098" relname="span">Pets have slightly different social norms</segment>
<segment id="97" parent="96" relname="antithesis">than people do ,</segment>
<segment id="98" parent="1098" relname="result">so it 's important that all household members learn how to interact appropriately with a pet .</segment>
<segment id="99" parent="1099" relname="sequence">Be gentle .</segment>
<segment id="100" parent="1100" relname="sequence">Never sneak up on a pet .</segment>
<segment id="101" parent="1101" relname="joint">Use your indoor voice .</segment>
<segment id="102" parent="1102" relname="sequence">Do n't shout or scream at a pet .</segment>
<segment id="103" parent="1103" relname="joint">Leave a sleeping pet alone .</segment>
<segment id="104" parent="1104" relname="joint">Do n't chase a pet .</segment>
<segment id="105" parent="1107" relname="joint">If a pet walks or runs away</segment>
<segment id="106" parent="1107" relname="joint">and wants to be alone ,</segment>
<segment id="107" parent="1106" relname="span">do n't pester it .</segment>
<segment id="108" parent="1109" relname="span">Do n't tease or take away a toy</segment>
<segment id="109" parent="108" relname="elaboration">the pet is playing with .</segment>
<segment id="110" parent="1111" relname="span">Leave the pet alone</segment>
<segment id="111" parent="110" relname="circumstance">when it is eating .</segment>
<segment id="112" parent="1113" relname="span">Explain how to tell</segment>
<segment id="113" parent="112" relname="condition">if a pet wants to be alone .</segment>
<segment id="114" parent="1114" relname="sequence">Different animals</segment>
<segment id="115" parent="1115" relname="sequence">Encourage the person to help with feeding/walking the pet .</segment>
<segment id="116" parent="1118" relname="sequence">Teach them how to fill the pet 's bowl</segment>
<segment id="117" parent="1118" relname="sequence">and store the food .</segment>
<segment id="118" parent="1120" relname="condition">If teaching about dogs ,</segment>
<segment id="119" parent="1120" relname="span">especially show them to never let a dog off of the leash ,</segment>
<segment id="120" parent="119" relname="condition">unless in a secured area .</segment>
<segment id="121" parent="1121" relname="joint">Walking and feeding pets is an important bonding experience .</segment>
<segment id="122" parent="1123" relname="span">Teach the person how to tell</segment>
<segment id="123" parent="122" relname="condition">if a pet is angry .</segment>
<segment id="124" parent="1126" relname="attribution">Tell them</segment>
<segment id="125" parent="1126" relname="joint">that growling/hissing are signs of anger ,</segment>
<segment id="126" parent="1126" relname="joint">and to slowly walk away .</segment>
<segment id="127" parent="1128" relname="span">Also , show the person not to touch the food bowl</segment>
<segment id="128" parent="1129" relname="contrast">while they 're eating ,</segment>
<segment id="129" parent="1129" relname="contrast">or take a toy away .</segment>
<segment id="130" parent="1130" relname="sequence">Tell them to never pull a pets tail .</segment>
<segment id="131" parent="1131" relname="sequence">Teach the person how to pet an animal gently .</segment>
<segment id="132" parent="1132" relname="contrast">Show them how to rub a dog 's belly ,</segment>
<segment id="133" parent="1132" relname="contrast">or pet a cat 's ears .</segment>
<segment id="134" parent="1134" relname="preparation">Tips</segment>
<segment id="135" parent="1134" relname="joint">Have patience .</segment>
<segment id="136" parent="1136" relname="span">Do n't force the person to help</segment>
<segment id="137" parent="136" relname="condition">if they 're afraid/upset .</segment>
<segment id="138" parent="1137" relname="span">Have the disabled person give treats to the new pet .</segment>
<segment id="139" parent="138" relname="motivation">This will help the pet like them .</segment>
